        <li> Smart watch integration</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="privacy-settings">Privacy & Settings</h2>
  <p>
    Maintain control over your data and privacy while enjoying smart notifications:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Data Usage</strong>: Control what data is used for generating notifications</li>
    <li><strong>Location Privacy</strong>: Choose precise or approximate location sharing</li>
    <li><strong>Analytics Opt-out</strong>: Disable notification performance tracking</li>
    <li><strong>Third-party Integration</strong>: Control connections with other apps and services</li>
    <li><strong>Data Retention</strong>: Set how long notification data is stored</li>
  </ul>

  <InfoBox type="warning" title="Battery Optimization">
    Smart notifications are designed to be battery-efficient. Location-based features use minimal power, and you can adjust settings to further optimize battery usage in Settings > Notifications > Battery Optimization.
  </InfoBox>

  <div class="my-6 bg-gradient-to-r from-neutral-50 to-gray-50 dark:from-neutral-800 dark:to-gray-800 p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-700">
